  "prompt": "Which is the best laptop to buy under 70k?",
  "response": "Choosing the best laptop under \u20b970,000 depends on your specific needs and preferences, such as desired performance, brand preference, and usage (gaming, content creation, general use, etc.). As of 2023, here are some popular and highly recommended laptops that fall under \u20b970,000 in India:\n\n1. **Acer Swift 3**\n   - Processor: Intel Core i5 or AMD Ryzen 5\n   - Display: 14-inch Full HD IPS\n   - RAM: 8GB\n   - Storage: 512GB SSD\n   - Features: Lightweight design, good battery life\n\n2. **HP Pavilion x360**\n   - Processor: Intel Core i5\n   - Display: 14-inch Full HD touch screen\n   - RAM: 8GB\n   - Storage: 512GB SSD\n   - Features: 2-in-1 convertible, good build quality\n\n3. **Dell Inspiron 15 5502**\n   - Processor: Intel Core i5\n   - Display: 15.6-inch Full HD\n   - RAM: 8GB\n   - Storage: 512GB SSD\n   - Features: Reliable performance, good display\n\n4. **ASUS VivoBook 15**\n   - Processor: AMD Ryzen 5 or Intel Core i5\n   - Display: 15.6-inch Full HD\n   - RAM: 8GB\n   - Storage: 512GB SSD\n   - Features: Sleek design, good value for money\n\n5. **Lenovo IdeaPad Slim 5i**\n   - Processor: Intel Core i5\n   - Display: 14-inch or 15.6-inch Full HD\n   - RAM: 8GB\n   - Storage: 512GB SSD\n   - Features: Solid performance, good battery life\n\n6. **Mi Notebook Horizon Edition 14**\n   - Processor: Intel Core i5\n   - Display: 14-inch Full HD\n   - RAM: 8GB\n   - Storage: 512GB SSD\n   - Features: Lightweight, slim bezels, good build quality\n\nWhen selecting a laptop, consider factors like build quality, brand reliability, after-sales service, and specific features such as battery life, portability, and screen quality. Reviews and customer feedback can also be helpful in making an informed decision.",
